## # Artifactory Remote Cargo Repository Resource

Provides an Artifactory remote `cargo` repository resource. This provides cargo specific fields and is the only way to get them
Official documentation can be found [here](https://www.jfrog.com/confluence/display/JFROG/Cargo+Registry)
## Note

If you get a 400 error: `"Custom Base URL should be defined prior to creating a Cargo repository"`,
you must set the base url at: `http://${host}/ui/admin/configuration/general`


{{% examples %}}

## Example Usage

{{< chooser language "typescript,python,go,csharp" / >}}





{{< example csharp >}}

```csharp
using Pulumi;
using Artifactory = Pulumi.Artifactory;

class MyStack : Stack
{
    public MyStack()
    {
        var my_remote_cargo = new Artifactory.RemoteCargoRepository("my-remote-cargo", new Artifactory.RemoteCargoRepositoryArgs
        {
            AnonymousAccess = true,
            GitRegistryUrl = "https://github.com/rust-lang/foo.index",
            Key = "my-remote-cargo",
        });
    }

}
```


{{< /example >}}


{{< example go >}}

```go
package main

import (
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi-artifactory/sdk/go/artifactory"
	"github.com/pulumi/pulumi/sdk/v3/go/pulumi"
)

func main() {
	pulumi.Run(func(ctx *pulumi.Context) error {
		_, err := artifactory.NewRemoteCargoRepository(ctx, "my_remote_cargo", &artifactory.RemoteCargoRepositoryArgs{
			AnonymousAccess: pulumi.Bool(true),
			GitRegistryUrl:  pulumi.String("https://github.com/rust-lang/foo.index"),
			Key:             pulumi.String("my-remote-cargo"),
		})
		if err != nil {
			return err
		}
		return nil
	})
}
```

direct repository-to-client streaming is used. This can be useful for multi-server setups over a high-speed LAN, with
one Artifactory caching certain data on central storage, and streaming it directly to satellite pass-though Artifactory
servers.

<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-optional"

any other host.

            title="Optional">
        <span id="state_anonymousaccess_csharp">

</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">bool</span>
    </dt>

{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="state_assumedofflineperiodsecs_csharp">

        <span class="property-type">bool</span>

            title="Optional">
        <span id="state_blockmismatchingmimetypes_csharp">
<a href="#state_blockmismatchingmimetypes_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Block<wbr>Mismatching<wbr>Mime<wbr>Types</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">bool</span>

HEAD requests are disallowed and therefore rejected, even though downloading the artifact is allowed. When checked,
Artifactory will bypass the HEAD request and cache the artifact directly using a GET request.
